1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,600
Ever since I started traveling with this front-opening case, I could never go back to my old one.

2
00:00:04,600 --> 00:00:19,800
It has a separate front compartment that pops open with one press. I keep my laptop and documents in that dedicated section, so at security I pull them straight out, no digging through everything. The front compartment even has its own combination lock, so security is never a worry.

3
00:00:19,800 --> 00:00:29,300
There's plenty of room, too. Thanks to the spacious deep compartment, it easily holds five to seven days of clothes, plus bulky, odd-shaped items, so for a trip this one case is all you need.

4
00:00:29,300 --> 00:00:38,500
The wheels are quiet T-P-E spinner wheels with built-in ball bearings and shock-absorbing springs, silent yet incredibly smooth, and durable enough that they won't wear out.

5
00:00:38,500 --> 00:00:46,600
The shell is pure polycarbonate, tough, scratch and impact resistant, and very light, which makes it especially friendly for anyone who isn't very strong.

6
00:00:46,600 --> 00:00:54,300
On the back there's a cup holder for your coffee, a charging port to top up your phone anytime, and an umbrella strap so you don't have to carry it, traveling with it feels like having a personal assistant.

7
00:00:54,300 --> 00:01:04,200
Best of all, the shop throws in a free set of colored wheels to mix and match, and if you'd rather not have wheels, you can swap in handles instead. Every detail is covered, this is the ideal travel case.
